A former governor of old Ondo State, Chief Bamidele Olumilua is dead. He died in the early hours of Thursday, according to Nigerian Tribune. Olumilua was governor between 1992 and 1993; he died at the age of 80. His eldest son and Commissioner for Information in Ekiti State, Mr Muyiwa Olumilua confirmed that his father died in his country home, Ikere-Ekiti. Details later… Source By Remi Koleoso   Ikere-Ekiti    -      An APC House of Representatives aspirant in Ekiti, Mr Muyiwa Olumilua, on Friday announced his withdrawal from the race fews days before the party primaries. Muyiwa, son of a former Governor of the old Ondo State, Evangelist Bamidele Olumilua, made his decision known to… September 21, 2018 In "News" Ariwodola Idowu Ado Ekiti - The Ekiti government has initiated plans to avert possible food shortage that may arise after the Covid-19 pandemic, the Commissioner for Information and Value Orientation, Chief Muyiwa Olumilua, has said. Olumilua said this on Thursday in Ado Ekiti at the end of the second virtual… April 23, 2020 In "News" FG Immortalises Late Adebayo, Names Varsity After Him May 20, 2017 In "News"